  {
    "ts": "2026-05-29T09:35:57+00:00",
    "headline": "Analysis-In China, AMD CEO Lisa Su is understated while Nvidia's Huang is more razzmatazz",
    "summary": "When AMD CEO Lisa Su arrived in China last week just days after Nvidia's CEO left, she kept a much lower profile than Jensen Huang, who drew crowds in the centre of the capital as he posed for photos and ate local ‌delicacies like Beijing-style soybean paste noodles.  Just a year ago at the annual Computex trade show in Taipei, Huang said Nvidia's market share in China had dropped to 50% from 95% due to U.S. export controls.  Since then, that ​has effectively fallen to zero, he said this year, amid Beijing's push for self-reliance in advanced AI chips.",
